The paper focuses on a robot system that learns visual representations through physical interactions with objects, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively discusses the use of ConvNets for visual representation learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to train the ConvNet, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neuron activations and nearest neighbor retrieval, which are common techniques in neural networks (cs.NE).
